Chastity

2013 Poem

The pain just as real as last time. For only five minutes, and then done. The knife just as quick. Through the left side of my labia, And then it’s done. Always down the same sixth grade anatomy- blood vessel and surprised nerves never severed. Each time, my 90-second blood shower is always accompanied by…

The color of what you don’t know, What is there. But there, wonder, between your fingers. I hold a handful of what is there. Fluff. Yellow. I desire, a burning thing, Freedom. A buried dead thing, Illusion. Something untouchable. Air. Grass. Gravity. Someone told me to be free, And let go of this tissue, Let…

“Deepl”
